@@ -0,0 +1,8 @@
+<div>
+    With this option checked, Hudson will not do a checkout from the SCM system 
+    for each configuration.
+    This can be usefull if your configuration can build concurrent from the same 
+    master source (e.g. via NFS/SMB), and it saves the time of the SCM-checkout.<br />
+    NB: The feature currently only works if a job is constranied to one node with
+    several executors, otherwise an exception will be thrown and the build will fail.
+</div>
